Essentially,
this is the essay I wish I could have read
before my youthful attempt to hike
from the South Rim to the river to the North Rim
on the South and North Kaibab Trails.

Because the hiker prepared to be led across the wide Canyon by geology
is the hiker who in fact will be tempted, deceived, and mislead by geology.

