We can imagine our hiker familiar with one last word: “Tapeats”.
While the Tapeats are not as famous as the ,
the hiker will have encountered them on day hikes —
they are the cap from which he has gazed from Plateau Point,
or the Great Unconformity along BAT.

So our hiker begins his descent
armed with a schematic view of the Canyon,
learned along the South Rim.

